(1, NULL, 'Generate questions based on Bloom’s Taxonomy', 'Use the updated Blooms Taxonomy framework, which replaces \"Synthesis\" with \"Create\" and focuses on action-based learning. Generate questions that encourage learners to engage in knowledge construction rather than passive recall. Prioritize questions that involve critical thinking, real-world application, and creative problem-solving.', '2025-02-19 16:34:11', NULL, 'Assessment'),
(2, NULL, 'Generate questions by Depth of Knowledge (DOK)', 'Structure questions according to Webb’s Depth of Knowledge framework. Generate basic recall questions for lower levels and progressively increase complexity. Create questions that require explanation and reasoning, followed by strategic thinking questions that involve decision-making and justification. At the highest level, develop extended thinking tasks that require synthesis of multiple ideas, evaluation, and long-term problem-solving.', '2025-02-19 16:34:11', NULL, 'Assessment'),
(3, NULL, 'Generate questions using Fink’s Learning Model', 'Create assessments that align with Fink’s six dimensions of learning. Start by testing foundational knowledge, then include tasks that require learners to apply what they have learned. Integrate ideas across different subjects and emphasize real-world relevance. Design prompts that encourage self-reflection, personal growth, and emotional engagement. Include activities that help learners develop independent learning strategies and critical thinking skills.', '2025-02-19 16:34:11', NULL, 'Assessment');

