\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\"}]}}]}\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Number of Questions Required: 15 (From 01/15 to 15/15)\\nLevels: [EASY, MEDIUM, DIFFICULT]\\nOutput Language: English (en)\\nQuestion Types: single_correct_questions, multiple_correct_questions, short_answer_questions, fill_up_blanks, long_answer_questions, match_the_following, true_false_questions, case_studies\\nSub Question Types: single_correct_questions, multiple_correct_questions, short_answer_questions, long_answer_questions, fill_up_blanks, match_the_following, true_false_questions\\nAdditional Instructions: Use the updated Blooms Taxonomy framework, which replaces \\\"Synthesis\\\" with \\\"Create\\\" and focuses on action-based learning. Generate questions that encourage learners to engage in knowledge construction rather than passive recall. Prioritize questions that involve critical thinking, real-world application, and creative problem-solving.\\nContext: ToC\\r\\nTOC\\r\\n1. Fundamentals of URLs\\r\\n1.1 Definition and Purpose of URLs\\r\\n1.2 Components of a URL Scheme, Host, Path, Query Parameters, Fragment)\\r\\n1.3 URL vs. URI vs. URN\\r\\n1.4 How URLs Work: Resolution and Resource Mapping\\r\\n2. URL Syntax and Encoding\\r\\n2.1 Standard URL Syntax RFC 3986\\r\\n2.2 Character Encoding in URLs Percent-Encoding)\\r\\n2.3 Reserved vs. Unreserved Characters\\r\\n2.4 Internationalized URLs IDN  Internationalized Domain Names)\\r\\n3. URL Handling in Web Technologies\\r\\n3.1 URLs in Web Browsers and HTTP Requests\\r\\n3.2 Client-Side URL Manipulation JavaScript, HTML5 APIs)\\r\\n3.3 Server-Side URL Handling Java, Python, Node.js, etc.)\\r\\n3.4 URL Parsing and Validation in Different Programming Languages\\r\\n4. Security Considerations in URLs\\r\\n4.1 Common URLBased Attacks Phishing, Open Redirects, SSRF, XSS\\r\\n4.2 Secure URL Handling Best Practices\\r\\n4.3 URL Encryption and Tokenization\\r\\n4.4 HTTP vs. HTTPS and Certificate Management\\r\\n5. SEO and Performance