umber\":\"06/15\",\"question\":\"Explain the difference between a URL and a URI.\",\"short_answer\":\"A URL is a specific type of URI that provides a means to locate a resource on the internet, while a URI can be a name, locator, or both.\",\"explanation\":\"URIs are a broader category that includes URLs and URNs. URLs specify locations.\",\"level\":\"MEDIUM\"},{\"number\":\"07/15\",\"question\":\"Describe the role of canonicalization in SEO.\",\"short_answer\":\"Canonicalization helps in preventing duplicate content issues by specifying a preferred URL for indexing by search engines.\",\"explanation\":\"Canonicalization tells search engines which version of a URL to index when there are multiple URLs for the same content.\",\"level\":\"DIFFICULT\"}],\"fill_up_blanks\":[{\"number\":\"08/15\",\"question\":\"A URL\'s [___] is used to separate the domain name from the specific resource path.\",\"correct_answer_text_list\":[\"path\"],\"explanation\":\"The path follows the domain in a URL and specifies the resource location.\",\"level\":\"EASY\"},{\"number\":\"09/15\",\"question\":\"In a URL, the [___] character is used to separate the query parameters from the rest of the URL.\",\"correct_answer_text_list\":[\"?\"],\"explanation\":\"The \'?\' character indicates the beginning of the query string in a URL.\",\"level\":\"MEDIUM\"}],\"long_answer_questions\":[{\"number\":\"10/15\",\"question\":\"Discuss the impact of URL shortening services on user privacy and security.\",\"long_answer\":\"URL shortening services can obscure the destination URL, leading to potential privacy and security risks as users cannot easily verify the target site before clicking. These services also introduce a dependency on third-party services, which could track user interactions or become unavailable, breaking the links.\",\"hint\":\"Consider how URL shortening can affect the visibility of the destination and the potential for misuse.\",\"explanation\":\"URL shortening can hide the actual URL, m