(10, '6d6a24ea8c10b11e8d6d92b8dfb66697', 7, 2, '{\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"system\",\"content\":\"# Instructions:\\n- Generate assessment questions based on the user\'s specified question types, difficulty levels, and total number of questions and output language and other configurations\\n- First, create a one short plan outlining the number of questions for each type, sub-type, and difficulty level, then follow the plan accordingly.\\n- Try to assign an equal number of questions to each type; if that\'s not possible, adjust the remaining questions as needed to fit.\\n- Create the questions in the exact JSON format provided, ensuring proper sequential numbering.\\n- Supported difficulty levels: EASY, MEDIUM, and DIFFICULT.\\n- Make sure the questions are not repetitive and on the same topic.\\n\\n## Sub-Question Instructions:\\n- Sub-questions are smaller, related questions that exist within a main question.\\n- Sub-questions **do not count** towards the total number of main questions. The specified number of main questions must still be generated.\\n- You are **not required to include all sub-question types** provided by the user. You can **select the most relevant sub-question types** based on the content of the main question.\\n- Each main question **must have a minimum of two sub-questions**.\\n\\n## Question Type Instructions:\\n- trueText and falseText should ideally be \'True\' or \'False\' in the specified language. If necessary, use close equivalents.\\n\\n\\n## Output Format:\\n- The output must be valid JSON, structured in **one line** and **compact format**, ensuring that all special characters, quotation marks, and line breaks are properly escaped to maintain a valid JSON format.\\n- **All content, including title, description, and questions, must be generated entirely in the user-requested output language.**\\n- If the provided context is in a different language than the requested output language, **use the context but generate the questions, title, and description strictly in the requested output language.**\\n\\n- JSON Schema: {\\\"plan_text_in_markdown_format\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"assessment_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"assessment_description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"single_correct_questions\\\":[{\\\"number\\\":\\\"n/10\\\",\\\"question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"choices\\\":[\\\"Choice 1 (Without Prefix like A), B),C) etc)\\\",\\\"Choice ...\\\",\\\"Choice 4\\\"],\\\"correct_answer_text\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"multiple_correct_questions\\\":[{\\\"number\\\":\\\"n/10\\\",\\\"question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"choices\\\":[\\\"Choice 1 (Without Prefix like A), B),C) etc)\\\",\\\"Choice ...\\\",\\\"Choice 4\\\"],\\\"correct_answer_text_list\\\":[],\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"short_answer_questions\\\":[{\\\"number\\\":\\\"n/10\\\",\\\"question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"short_answer\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"long_answer_questions\\\":[{\\\"number\\\":\\\"n/10\\\",\\\"question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"long_answer\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"hint\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"fill_up_blanks\\\":[{\\\"number\\\":\\\"n/10\\\",\\\"question\\\":\\\"Use [___] as a placeholder for blanks. Ensure each blank has exactly one answer. For multiple blanks, answers must match the number of blanks.\\\",\\\"correct_answer_text_list\\\":[],\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"true_false_questions\\\":[{\\\"number\\\":\\\"n/10\\\",\\\"question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"trueText\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"falseText\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"correct_answer_text\\\":\\\"true or false boolean value\\\",\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"match_the_following\\\":[{\\\"number\\\":\\\"n/10\\\",\\\"question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"pairs\\\":{\\\"pair 1\\\":\\\"pair 1 answer\\\",\\\"pair 2\\\":\\\"pair 2 answer\\\",\\\"pair ...\\\":\\\"pair ... answer\\\"},\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"case_studies\\\":[{\\\"number\\\":\\\"n/10\\\",\\\"main_question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"sub_question\\\":{\\\"single_correct_questions\\\":[{\\\"question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"choices\\\":[\\\"Choice 1 (Without Prefix like A), B),C) etc)\\\",\\\"Choice ...\\\",\\\"Choice 4\\\"],\\\"correct_answer_text\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"multiple_correct_questions\\\":[{\\\"question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"choices\\\":[\\\"Choice 1 (Without Prefix like A), B),C) etc)\\\",\\\"Choice ...\\\",\\\"Choice 4\\\"],\\\"correct_answer_text_list\\\":[],\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"short_answer_questions\\\":[{\\\"question\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"short_answer\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"level\\\":\\\"\\\"}]}}]}\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Number of Questions Required: 10 (From 01/10 to 10/10)\\nLevels: [EASY, MEDIUM, DIFFICULT]\\nOutput Language: English (en)\\nQuestion Types: single_correct_questions, multiple_correct_questions, short_answer_questions, match_the_following, fill_up_blanks, long_answer_questions, true_false_questions, case_studies\\nSub Question Types: single_correct_questions, multiple_correct_questions, short_answer_questions\\nContext: Intelligent Assessments \\t\\t11th April 2025\\nEffortless Mastery \\t\\t\\t04:11 PM\\n\\n\\nASHA Training and Health Services Overview\\n\\nQ1. What is the primary role of an ASHA worker? (Single Select)\\na) To act as a bridge between rural people and health services (Correct Answer)\\nb) To provide advanced medical treatment\\nc) To replace doctors in villages\\nd) To manage village finances\\nExplanation: ASHA workers are trained to connect rural populations with healthcare services and facilitate community health goals.\\nQ2. What is the main goal of the National Rural Health Mission? (Single Select)\\na) To build more hospitals\\nb) To provide effective, efficient, and affordable healthcare to rural populations (Correct Answer)\\nc) To increase urban health services\\nd) To create more medical colleges\\nExplanation: The National Rural Health Mission aims to improve healthcare access and quality in rural areas.\\nQ3. Which vaccine is given to prevent Tuberculosis in children? (Single Select)\\na) BCG (Correct Answer)\\nb) Polio\\nc) DPT\\nd) Measles\\nExplanation: BCG vaccine is administered to prevent tuberculosis in children.\\nQ4. Which of the following are tasks performed by ASHA workers? (Multiple Select)\\na) Immunization of children (Correct Answer)\\nb) Conducting surgeries\\nc) Providing antenatal care (Correct Answer)\\nd) Managing village water supply\\nExplanation: ASHA workers are responsible for immunizing children and providing antenatal care but do not conduct surgeries or manage water supplies.\\nQ5. What are the key components of the National Rural Health Mission? (Multiple Select)\\na) Provision of a female health activist in each village (Correct Answer)\\nb) Architectural correction of the health system (Correct Answer)\\nc) Increasing urban healthcare budget\\nd) Integration of vertical Health and Family Welfare Programs (Correct Answer)\\nExplanation: The mission focuses on providing female health activists, correcting health system architecture, and integrating health and welfare programs.\\nQ6. What are the benefits of breastfeeding according to the ASHA training manual? (Multiple Select)\\na) Provides immunity to the baby (Correct Answer)\\nb) Helps in birth control (Correct Answer)\\nc) Increases mother\'s weight\\nd) Reduces risk of breast cancer\\nExplanation: Breastfeeding provides immunity to the baby and can help in birth control by delaying the return of the menstrual cycle.\\nQ7. What is the purpose of the Janani Suraksha Yojana? (Short Answer)\\nAnswer: To reduce maternal and neonatal mortality by promoting institutional delivery among poor pregnant women.\\nExplanation: The Janani Suraksha Yojana provides financial incentives to encourage institutional deliveries, thereby reducing risks associated with home births.\\nQ8. What are the six \'clean\' practices a Dai must follow during childbirth? (Short Answer)\\nAnswer: Clean place, clean hands, clean perineum, clean thread, clean blade, clean cloth.\\nExplanation: These practices ensure a hygienic environment to prevent infections during childbirth.\\nQ9. Explain the role of ASHA workers in the National Rural Health Mission and how they contribute to achieving its goals. (Long Answer)\\nAnswer: ASHA workers are the frontline health workers in rural areas, acting as a bridge between the community and healthcare services. They are responsible for promoting health awareness, facilitating access to healthcare, providing basic medical care, and supporting maternal and child health initiatives. By performing tasks such as immunization, health education, and community mobilization, they contribute significantly to achieving the goals of the National Rural Health Mission, which include improving healthcare delivery, reducing health disparities, and enhancing the overall health of rural populations.\\nHint: Discuss ASHA\'s responsibilities, training, and impact on community health.\\nExplanation: ASHA workers play a crucial role in community health by providing essential services and bridging gaps between the community and healthcare systems, thereby supporting the mission\'s objectives.\\nQ10. Describe the importance of personal hygiene as outlined in the ASHA training manual and its impact on community health. (Long Answer)\\nAnswer: Personal hygiene is emphasized in the ASHA training manual as a fundamental aspect of health. It includes practices such as regular handwashing, maintaining clean teeth, cutting nails, daily bathing, wearing clean clothes, and proper toilet practices. These practices are crucial in preventing the spread of diseases such as diarrhea, dysentery, cholera, skin infections, and dental problems. By promoting personal hygiene, ASHA workers help reduce the incidence of illness in the community, improve overall health, and contribute to a cleaner and healthier living environment.\\nHint: Focus on specific hygiene practices and their health benefits.\\nExplanation: Personal hygiene is essential for preventing disease and maintaining health. ASHA workers educate communities on hygiene to reduce health risks and promote well-being.\\n\\n\"}]}', NULL, '{\"plan_text_in_markdown_format\":\"1. Single Correct Questions: 2 (1 EASY, 1 MEDIUM)\\n2. Multiple Correct Questions: 1 (DIFFICULT)\\n3. Short Answer Questions: 1 (MEDIUM)\\n4. Long Answer Questions: 1 (DIFFICULT)\\n5. Fill Up Blanks: 1 (EASY)\\n6. True/False Questions: 1 (EASY)\\n7. Match the Following: 1 (MEDIUM)\\n8. Case Studies: 2 (1 MEDIUM, 1 DIFFICULT)\",\"assessment_title\":\"ASHA Training and Health Services Assessment\",\"assessment_description\":\"This assessment evaluates the understanding of ASHA Training and Health Services, focusing on the role of ASHA workers, health initiatives, and practices outlined in the ASHA training manual.\",\"single_correct_questions\":[{\"number\":\"01/10\",\"question\":\"What is the primary focus of ASHA workers in their community role?\",\"choices\":[\"Promoting health awareness and education\",\"Providing advanced medical care\",\"Managing financial services\",\"Building health infrastructure\"],\"correct_answer_text\":\"Promoting health awareness and education\",\"explanation\":\"ASHA workers are mainly involved in health promotion and education to improve community health outcomes.\",\"level\":\"EASY\"},{\"number\":\"02/10\",\"question\":\"Which initiative primarily aims to reduce infant mortality in rural areas?\",\"choices\":[\"Janani Suraksha Yojana\",\"National Urban Health Mission\",\"Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana\",\"Beti Bachao Beti Padhao\"],\"correct_answer_text\":\"Janani Suraksha Yojana\",\"explanation\":\"Janani Suraksha Yojana is focused on promoting institutional deliveries to reduce infant and maternal mortality.\",\"level\":\"MEDIUM\"}],\"multiple_correct_questions\":[{\"number\":\"03/10\",\"question\":\"Which are the critical roles played by ASHA workers in community health?\",\"choices\":[\"Conducting health surveys\",\"Providing antenatal care\",\"Delivering advanced surgical procedures\",\"Facilitating child immunization programs\"],\"correct_answer_text_list\":[\"Conducting health surveys\",\"Providing antenatal care\",\"Facilitating child immunization programs\"],\"explanation\":\"ASHA workers conduct health surveys, provide antenatal care, and facilitate immunization but do not perform surgical procedures.\",\"level\":\"DIFFICULT\"}],\"short_answer_questions\":[{\"number\":\"04/10\",\"question\":\"What is the role of ASHA workers in promoting family planning?\",\"short_answer\":\"ASHA workers educate families about family planning methods and distribute contraceptives to ensure informed choices are made.\",\"explanation\":\"ASHA workers play a crucial role in family planning by providing information and resources to manage and plan family growth effectively.\",\"level\":\"MEDIUM\"}],\"long_answer_questions\":[{\"number\":\"05/10\",\"question\":\"Discuss how ASHA workers contribute to improving maternal health in rural areas.\",\"long_answer\":\"ASHA workers contribute to maternal health by promoting antenatal care, ensuring institutional deliveries, educating women on nutrition, and advocating for regular health check-ups. They support pregnant women through prenatal, delivery, and postnatal stages, ensuring that mothers receive necessary healthcare services. Their efforts lead to reduced maternal and neonatal mortality rates and improved health outcomes for mothers and babies.\",\"hint\":\"Focus on antenatal care, institutional delivery, and education.\",\"explanation\":\"Through education, support, and facilitation of healthcare services, ASHA workers significantly improve maternal health in rural communities.\",\"level\":\"DIFFICULT\"}],\"fill_up_blanks\":[{\"number\":\"06/10\",\"question\":\"The ASHA wo