 primary role of an ASHA worker?\",\"choices\":[\"Providing basic healthcare services\",\"Managing hospital administration\",\"Performing surgical operations\",\"Conducting laboratory tests\"],\"correct_answer_text\":\"Providing basic healthcare services\",\"explanation\":\"ASHA workers are primarily responsible for providing basic healthcare services in rural areas.\",\"level\":\"EASY\"},{\"number\":\"02/10\",\"question\":\"Which among the following is a responsibility of ASHA workers in maternal health?\",\"choices\":[\"Conducting surgeries\",\"Providing antenatal care\",\"Administering anesthesia\",\"Performing blood transfusions\"],\"correct_answer_text\":\"Providing antenatal care\",\"explanation\":\"ASHA workers play a key role in providing antenatal care to pregnant women.\",\"level\":\"MEDIUM\"}],\"multiple_correct_questions\":[{\"number\":\"03/10\",\"question\":\"Which of the following tasks are performed by ASHA workers?\",\"choices\":[\"Promoting immunization\",\"Educating on nutrition\",\"Organizing health camps\",\"Performing complex surgeries\"],\"correct_answer_text_list\":[\"Promoting immunization\",\"Educating on nutrition\",\"Organizing health camps\"],\"explanation\":\"ASHA workers are involved in promoting immunization, educating on nutrition, and organizing health camps. They do not perform surgeries.\",\"level\":\"DIFFICULT\"}],\"short_answer_questions\":[{\"number\":\"04/10\",\"question\":\"Describe a key responsibility of ASHA workers in the context of child healthcare.\",\"short_answer\":\"ASHA workers are responsible for promoting immunization and monitoring child growth.\",\"explanation\":\"A key responsibility of ASHA workers includes ensuring that children receive timely immunizations and monitoring their growth and development.\",\"level\":\"MEDIUM\"}],\"long_answer_questions\":[{\"number\":\"05/10\",\"question\":\"Discuss the impact of ASHA workers on rural healthcare systems in India.\",\"long_answer\":\"ASHA workers have significantl