adha@gmail.com Providing basic healthcare services Providing antenatal care Promoting immunization\\nEducating on nutrition\\nOrganizing health camps of ASHA workers in the context of child healthcare. Focus on the roles, responsibilities, and outcomes of ASHA workers. Fill up 1: education False\\n\\nDesired Output Length: with minimal explanation(approx: 100-150 words based on the context)\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Query: ASHA full form?\"}]}', NULL, '<h1>ASHA Full Form Inquiry</h1>\n<main>\n  <p>The full form of <em>ASHA</em> is <em>Accredited Social Health Activist</em>. ASHA workers are community health workers instituted by the government of India’s Ministry of Health and Family Welfare as part of the National Rural Health Mission (NRHM). They play a crucial role in connecting rural populations to healthcare services and promoting health awareness at the community level.</p>\n</main>', '2025-04-11 16:59:45.268865');
