(59, 6, NULL, 6, 'TEXTAREA', 'Difficult', 'Discuss the cultural and health implications of bathing daily in different climates.', 'Discuss the cultural and health implications of bathing daily in different climates.', NULL, '{\"answer\": \"Daily bathing is culturally viewed as a ritual of cleanliness and is essential in hot climates due to excessive sweating, preventing body odor and skin infections. However, in colder climates, daily bathing might not be necessary, and excessive bathing can lead to dry skin. Adjusting bathing frequency according to the climate while maintaining personal hygiene practices is crucial.\"}', 'Consider the necessity of daily bathing in hot versus cold climates.', 'The need for daily bathing varies with climate; in hot climates, it prevents skin-related issues from sweat, while in cold climates, it may lead to dry skin if overdone.', 1.00, NULL, 0, '2025-04-12 10:00:07.389093', '2025-04-12 10:00:07.389093'),
